- Yes?
- Got any brilliant ideas?

00:17:18.238 --> 00:17:20.472
They say Gen Z these days
come up with fresh, creative ideas,

00:17:20.472 --> 00:17:23.305
but I guess not all of them do.

00:17:25.505 --> 00:17:27.605
You must've learned something in a month.

00:17:27.605 --> 00:17:29.305
Didn't your supervisor teach you anything?

00:17:29.305 --> 00:17:30.805
Just scold me already.

00:17:30.805 --> 00:17:32.505
I think that's what you wanted to say to me.

00:17:32.505 --> 00:17:34.972
Fine, you talk well.

00:17:34.972 --> 00:17:36.338
Now, show me what you've got.

00:17:36.338 --> 00:17:38.838
Set an example as a senior.

00:17:40.372 --> 00:17:43.872
You think you can just sit back
now that Germany's basically a done deal?

00:17:43.872 --> 00:17:48.672
I suppose that's smarter than getting
involved and docking your own score.

00:17:52.838 --> 00:17:55.072
So, I just need to bring it
by the next meeting, right?

00:17:55.072 --> 00:17:58.972
A groundbreaking idea to boost beer sales?

00:18:01.638 --> 00:18:03.572
So, you went head-to-head
with your boss again?

00:18:03.572 --> 00:18:07.705
I worked all weekend because of her,
and now she's messing with my junior.

00:18:07.705 --> 00:18:09.938
Why's she always obsessed
with taking me down?

00:18:09.938 --> 00:18:14.038
Because a junior who's better
than her keeps threatening her turf.

00:18:14.038 --> 00:18:16.905
She blames you for last year's
failed promotion, right?

00:18:16.905 --> 00:18:18.272
No, that was

00:18:18.272 --> 00:18:21.572
because she tried to claim
our team's all-nighter as her work.

00:18:21.572 --> 00:18:24.905
Anyway, I stormed out in anger earlier,

00:18:24.905 --> 00:18:28.372
but where do I find such an idea?

00:18:28.372 --> 00:18:30.272
Took a while to find.

00:19:07.072 --> 00:19:11.238
You were a handful in middle school,
and you still are.

00:19:17.238 --> 00:19:19.205
[14 years ago]

00:19:19.205 --> 00:19:20.869
[Cha Min Uk]

00:19:23.805 --> 00:19:27.105
At this point, you owe your knees an apology.

00:19:28.805 --> 00:19:30.472
It hurts.

00:19:30.472 --> 00:19:32.172
Stop whining.

00:19:53.572 --> 00:19:55.305
Here too.

00:20:05.605 --> 00:20:07.338
Are you okay?

00:20:29.972 --> 00:20:32.238
Had a blind date over the weekend?

00:20:32.238 --> 00:20:33.805
Did Mi Ran say that?

00:20:33.805 --> 00:20:36.372
No, I was hoping the three of us
could grab a drink after so long.

00:20:36.372 --> 00:20:38.572
But she said you have a very important date.

00:20:39.205 --> 00:20:41.872
No, it's not that. Not at all.

00:20:41.872 --> 00:20:46.338
I thought maybe you'd finally
started thinking about marriage.

00:20:46.338 --> 00:20:48.272
You know how my parents are.

00:20:48.272 --> 00:20:50.272
Get out! Get out!

00:20:50.272 --> 00:20:51.772
Why should I leave? This is my house!

00:20:51.772 --> 00:20:52.938
Since when?

00:20:52.938 --> 00:20:55.172
How could you do this to us?

00:20:55.172 --> 00:20:58.005
Dad, Dad!

00:20:58.005 --> 00:21:00.172
Dad, please don't go.

00:21:00.172 --> 00:21:03.205
Dad, please don't go.

00:21:03.205 --> 00:21:05.572
Dad.

00:21:05.572 --> 00:21:07.905
Dad.

00:21:09.405 --> 00:21:10.405
Huh?

00:21:10.405 --> 00:21:14.138
You still think your parents' divorce
was your fault?

00:21:14.138 --> 00:21:16.205
So, why would anyone marry without love?

00:21:16.205 --> 00:21:19.838
Even if it hadn't been Dad's affair,
they would've divorced anyway.

00:21:19.838 --> 00:21:21.805
They weren't compatible.

00:21:21.805 --> 00:21:25.405
When well-matched people meet,
they might go a lifetime without fighting.

00:21:25.405 --> 00:21:26.505
Then, you...

00:21:26.505 --> 00:21:30.572
Even if you meet someone
you truly love later, you won't marry?

00:21:30.572 --> 00:21:31.572
Huh?

00:21:31.572 --> 00:21:32.638
Never mind.

00:21:32.638 --> 00:21:36.438
Why am I asking so much
to someone who prioritizes work?

00:21:41.272 --> 00:21:43.538
I should go. The team leader called for me.

00:21:43.538 --> 00:21:47.305
Ah, what? You said you'd help me
figure out the beer issue.

00:21:49.072 --> 00:21:50.705
Don't overthink it.

00:21:50.705 --> 00:21:53.972
Being overly cautious can be poison.

00:21:53.972 --> 00:21:57.005
The path lies where you seek the answer.

00:21:57.005 --> 00:21:59.705
Beer problems get solved at a pub.

00:21:59.705 --> 00:22:01.138
I'll get going.

00:22:01.138 --> 00:22:03.338
Hey.

00:22:03.338 --> 00:22:05.038
I really have to go.

00:22:11.805 --> 00:22:14.838
I became more careful because of you...

00:22:22.693 --> 00:22:24.613
Oh.

00:22:26.405 --> 00:22:27.749
What brings you here?

00:22:27.749 --> 00:22:29.305
Hey.

00:22:29.305 --> 00:22:31.472
Say hello to him.

00:22:31.472 --> 00:22:33.638
This is Manager Song, a good friend of mine.

00:22:33.638 --> 00:22:36.538
Pleased to meet you. I'm Manager Song.

00:22:40.972 --> 00:22:44.293
Apologies, but I need to step out.
Please get straight to the point.

00:22:44.293 --> 00:22:45.701
Huh?

00:22:45.701 --> 00:22:48.938
Oh.

00:22:48.938 --> 00:22:53.438
You remember the commercial
building project I mentioned before?

00:22:53.438 --> 00:22:56.238
I was thinking of doing that
together with Manager Song.

00:22:56.238 --> 00:22:57.905
I believe I addressed that last time.

00:22:57.905 --> 00:22:59.405
There's already a qualified person for that.

00:22:59.405 --> 00:23:04.738
More importantly, Q2 operating profits
for the resort business hit a historic low.

00:23:04.738 --> 00:23:07.172
With your approval, Vice Chairman,
I'll reassign the lead.

00:23:07.172 --> 00:23:09.405
Are you saying you'll fire Team Leader Park?

00:23:09.405 --> 00:23:13.138
More like relocating the team
to a suitable position.

00:23:13.138 --> 00:23:14.838
No, but still...

00:23:14.838 --> 00:23:18.605
Team Leader Park has handled
the resort project since the beginning...

00:23:18.605 --> 00:23:21.038
Compensation is repaid with results.

00:23:21.038 --> 00:23:22.505
Not loyalty or diligence.

00:23:22.505 --> 00:23:24.738
If there's nothing else, I'll take my leave.

00:23:24.738 --> 00:23:26.472
I have a meeting.

00:23:30.105 --> 00:23:32.772
That insolent little...

00:23:43.038 --> 00:23:44.838
That's right, that's right.

00:23:44.838 --> 00:23:46.738
Oh, yeah.

00:23:49.472 --> 00:23:51.038
Oh, you're here.

00:23:51.038 --> 00:23:52.238
Doing this at the office too?

00:23:52.238 --> 00:23:53.538
Wrong question.

00:23:53.538 --> 00:23:55.372
I can only do this at work.

00:23:55.372 --> 00:23:57.772
Your mom would smack my back if she saw this.

00:23:57.772 --> 00:23:59.438
That's right, that's right.

00:23:59.438 --> 00:24:01.105
Mom's still really mad, huh?

00:24:01.105 --> 00:24:03.772
She's always been like that.

00:24:03.772 --> 00:24:05.838
[Finish]
That's right, yay!

00:24:05.838 --> 00:24:07.672
[Mari]
I came in first place.

00:24:07.672 --> 00:24:10.705
This game's great for relieving stress.

00:24:13.305 --> 00:24:15.238
Still busy these days?

00:24:15.238 --> 00:24:17.305
Rumor has it you're working like a warrior.

00:24:17.305 --> 00:24:19.805
I'm just doing what needs to be done.

00:24:24.705 --> 00:24:26.605
That gesture with your hand...

00:24:29.172 --> 00:24:30.405
Never mind.

00:24:30.405 --> 00:24:33.338
Ah, Du Jun, first you need
recognition from the board.

00:24:33.338 --> 00:24:36.672
It seems Moo Young is trying
to shake up the board with this issue.

00:24:36.672 --> 00:24:38.938
Now, hand over
the trading company affairs to me.

00:24:38.938 --> 00:24:40.538
- Father.
- Instead, from now on,

00:24:40.538 --> 00:24:43.305
you report to Taehan Liquor.

00:24:44.472 --> 00:24:47.205
As president, not managing director.

00:24:54.005 --> 00:24:58.305
With spicy greasy food, lagers
completely lose their flavor and aroma.

00:24:58.305 --> 00:24:59.805
'You're better off with something aromatic.'

00:24:59.805 --> 00:25:01.972
'Stout works well, IPA's fine too.'

00:25:01.972 --> 00:25:04.472
I want to tell them that.

00:25:04.472 --> 00:25:06.372
But I should hold back, right?

00:25:09.672 --> 00:25:11.205
Do you know him?

00:25:11.205 --> 00:25:14.772
Huh? No, nothing.

00:25:14.772 --> 00:25:15.772
Boyfriend?

00:25:15.772 --> 00:25:18.372
Ugh, your face turned bright red.

00:25:18.372 --> 00:25:20.538
He's a bit older, but a total romantic.

00:25:20.538 --> 00:25:24.638
Though whether it's 3 months or 30 years,
we'll have to live together to find out.

00:25:24.638 --> 00:25:26.605
Live together?

00:25:26.605 --> 00:25:30.372
Cohabitation. I firmly believe in
living together before marriage.

00:25:30.372 --> 00:25:31.805
Well, true.

00:25:31.805 --> 00:25:34.238
Breaking up is better than getting divorced.

00:25:34.238 --> 00:25:36.472
You have a boyfriend, right, Manager?

00:25:36.472 --> 00:25:38.872
Someone this perfect
can't possibly be single.

00:25:38.872 --> 00:25:39.972
I'm dying to know.

00:25:39.972 --> 00:25:42.405
What kind of unicorn is your boyfriend?

00:25:42.405 --> 00:25:43.772
Unicorn?

00:25:43.772 --> 00:25:47.505
Makes sense. I've never seen him.

00:25:48.272 --> 00:25:49.938
Let's drink. Drink.

00:25:49.938 --> 00:25:51.538
Here.

00:25:51.538 --> 00:25:53.238
Cheers!

00:25:59.589 --> 00:26:03.172
[Min Uk]

00:26:03.172 --> 00:26:06.372
Did you get off work? Have you eaten?

00:26:14.938 --> 00:26:16.005
I'm dying to know.

00:26:16.005 --> 00:26:18.205
What kind of unicorn is your boyfriend?

00:26:18.205 --> 00:26:21.805
When well-matched people meet,
they might go a lifetime without fighting.

00:26:21.805 --> 00:26:26.872
Even if you meet someone
you truly love later, you won't marry?

00:26:26.872 --> 00:26:29.638
Yeah, someone like Min Uk would be fine.

00:26:29.638 --> 00:26:31.572
Ugh, what am I even thinking right now?

00:26:31.572 --> 00:26:33.405
Get a grip.

00:26:40.705 --> 00:26:46.053
[Did you get off work? Have you eaten?]

00:26:47.738 --> 00:26:49.938
He should be off work by now.

00:26:49.938 --> 00:26:51.838
Did he pass out from exhaustion?

00:26:59.705 --> 00:27:03.472
I even bought tteokbokki
from his favorite spot.

00:27:03.472 --> 00:27:05.138
But he's not answering.

00:27:05.138 --> 00:27:07.605
It's only good for Hwang Mi Ran, then.

00:27:10.838 --> 00:27:13.072
Why is she out there?

00:27:16.372 --> 00:27:18.138
Cha Min Uk?

00:28:04.005 --> 00:28:05.893
I told you about her, right? It's Mi Ran.

00:28:05.893 --> 00:28:08.138
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

00:28:08.138 --> 00:28:09.905
I even have someone I like.

00:28:09.905 --> 00:28:11.272
Oh you? Who?

00:28:24.605 --> 00:28:25.972
You report to Taehan Liquor.

00:28:25.972 --> 00:28:28.005
As president, not managing director.

00:28:39.941 --> 00:28:41.938
Oh, no.

00:28:41.938 --> 00:28:46.072
Why did it have to spill out like this?

00:29:10.638 --> 00:29:12.741
[Chapter 4 Fate]

00:29:15.538 --> 00:29:16.869
What?

00:29:18.949 --> 00:29:20.869
Darn it.

00:29:26.005 --> 00:29:27.105
Hey!

00:29:27.105 --> 00:29:29.472
Come out here, please!

00:29:29.472 --> 00:29:33.172
How could you do this to me, huh?

00:29:33.172 --> 00:29:35.405
What did I do wrong?

00:29:35.405 --> 00:29:38.905
Why are you treating me like this?

00:29:40.572 --> 00:29:42.772
What? Is she drunk?

00:29:43.905 --> 00:29:45.572
I'm sorry.

00:29:45.572 --> 00:29:47.372
I'll compensate you however much you want.

00:29:47.372 --> 00:29:50.505
You could've at least given me a heads-up.

00:29:50.505 --> 00:29:54.338
How could you stab me in the back like this?

00:29:56.338 --> 00:29:58.538
What's wrong with her?

00:30:01.372 --> 00:30:03.238
I'm sorry.

00:30:03.238 --> 00:30:04.972
Hey there.

00:30:05.638 --> 00:30:07.872
Why is your tint so dark?

00:30:09.238 --> 00:30:11.538
Hey! Hey!

00:30:11.538 --> 00:30:13.972
What are you doing in there?

00:30:15.138 --> 00:30:16.872
Hey!

00:30:22.138 --> 00:30:24.605
Hey! Don't you dare drive away!

00:30:24.605 --> 00:30:26.405
That crazy...

00:30:26.405 --> 00:30:28.389
[Check: One million won]
Jeez.

00:30:31.205 --> 00:30:34.305
Is... he an angel?

00:30:35.638 --> 00:30:40.405
Suddenly telling me to buy
every type of beer? What now?

00:30:40.405 --> 00:30:41.705
Whew, almost had a disaster today.

00:30:41.705 --> 00:30:44.072
Goodness, is our director
going through puberty?

00:30:44.072 --> 00:30:45.238
You're drinking beer
you normally wouldn't touch...

00:30:45.238 --> 00:30:46.638
You just decided to run wild?

00:30:46.638 --> 00:30:49.572
What are you talking about?
I was holding back before.

00:30:49.572 --> 00:30:51.138
And now?

00:30:51.138 --> 00:30:53.105
Because I need it now.

00:30:53.938 --> 00:30:57.372
Have you ever had a drink with me
besides during study abroad?

00:30:57.372 --> 00:31:01.072
Back then, I felt sorry for you
whining about having no friends.

00:31:01.072 --> 00:31:03.572
Anyway, as of today, I'm stepping back from
the foundation and trading company.

00:31:03.572 --> 00:31:04.738
What?

00:31:04.738 --> 00:31:07.238
Once the handover is done, I'll
start at Taehan Liquor immediately.

00:31:07.238 --> 00:31:09.505
No, wait. Suddenly?

00:31:09.505 --> 00:31:13.038
Giving up something good
for gossip-filled Taehan Liquor...

00:31:14.005 --> 00:31:15.638
Demand it confidently from the chairman.

00:31:15.638 --> 00:31:18.272
Tell him you have something
you want to do! A dream!

00:31:18.272 --> 00:31:20.038
Do I even have something like that?

00:31:20.038 --> 00:31:23.472
Anyway, schedule me for
all liquor-related events going forward.

00:31:23.472 --> 00:31:27.572
And make sure to clip every article
about competitors, got it?

00:31:28.505 --> 00:31:31.738
- Got it.
- Why drink before finishing the work?

00:31:35.005 --> 00:31:36.705
Huh?

00:31:57.638 --> 00:31:59.438
What?

00:32:00.605 --> 00:32:02.372
Just go.

00:32:14.053 --> 00:32:16.305
Darn, I really want a drink.

00:32:21.172 --> 00:32:23.138
I'm sending you because
you said you wanted a drink.

00:32:23.138 --> 00:32:25.705
You know that Yellow beer launched in Korea?

00:32:25.705 --> 00:32:28.972
The party's there today,
at the flagship store in Itaewon.

00:32:28.972 --> 00:32:33.221
Just make a good impression
and capture the vibe of the place.

00:32:33.221 --> 00:32:34.693
Come on!

00:32:49.829 --> 00:32:51.397
[Yellow Beer]

00:32:56.405 --> 00:32:58.405
Perfect timing.

00:32:58.405 --> 00:33:00.572
I was craving a drink.

00:33:00.572 --> 00:33:02.305
Ta-da!

00:33:03.805 --> 00:33:08.305
Ah, mixing it like that ruins the flavor.

00:33:09.005 --> 00:33:10.638
Jang Hui Won, calm down.

00:33:10.638 --> 00:33:15.672
Just drink quietly and don't meddle today.

00:33:15.672 --> 00:33:17.372
Calm down.

00:33:22.772 --> 00:33:26.238
Drink, drink, drink.

00:33:26.238 --> 00:33:28.038
Take it easy. Are you here to party?

00:33:28.038 --> 00:33:30.738
So Du Jun's here to study, huh?

00:33:30.738 --> 00:33:32.072
You go home first.

00:33:32.072 --> 00:33:33.838
I'm not going home today.

00:33:33.838 --> 00:33:36.438
No, I can't go home. I can't.

00:33:36.438 --> 00:33:39.072
Want me to ban you from the office too?

00:33:42.238 --> 00:33:44.605
Don't look at me like that.

00:33:44.605 --> 00:33:47.272
I'm so stressed. Just seeing your face...

00:33:47.272 --> 00:33:49.238
Don't you know I have a sensitive stomach?

00:33:49.238 --> 00:33:51.038
I really have stomach trouble...

00:33:52.272 --> 00:33:53.905
I've got the signal...
Gotta run to the bathroom.

00:33:53.905 --> 00:33:55.805
- Here we go again.
- Jeez.

00:33:55.805 --> 00:33:57.838
Bathroom! Bathroom!

00:34:00.538 --> 00:34:03.672
Jeez, I should really need to
handle things alone next time.

00:34:12.638 --> 00:34:14.438
Why does it taste like this?

00:34:20.205 --> 00:34:22.338
Wait, that woman...

00:34:26.705 --> 00:34:28.505
That crazy woman from back then.

00:34:28.505 --> 00:34:30.405
Oh no, I could get in trouble.

00:34:31.638 --> 00:34:34.038
- You scared me!
- What now, again?

00:34:34.038 --> 00:34:36.638
Again? Do you know me?

00:34:36.638 --> 00:34:39.072
No, I absolutely don't know you.

00:34:40.405 --> 00:34:44.072
But isn't this a bit much?

00:34:44.072 --> 00:34:45.805
What do you mean?

00:34:57.905 --> 00:35:00.105
When pouring wheat beer,

00:35:00.105 --> 00:35:04.472
tilt the glass at 45 degrees
and fill only 70%.

00:35:05.205 --> 00:35:06.469
Then,

00:35:06.469 --> 00:35:07.959
[Yeast]
you should pour in the rest

00:35:07.959 --> 00:35:09.405
including the settled yeast

00:35:09.405 --> 00:35:11.838
to deepen the flavor.

00:35:35.238 --> 00:35:37.317
Finish it

00:35:37.317 --> 00:35:39.038
with this caramel popcorn.

00:35:39.038 --> 00:35:43.038
The sweet-salty combo
will balance the subtle bitterness.

00:35:54.772 --> 00:35:56.505
How is it?

00:36:01.705 --> 00:36:04.238
I'll take my leave then.

00:36:04.238 --> 00:36:07.372
Are you some kind of
beer expert or something?

00:36:07.372 --> 00:36:08.938
Pardon?

00:36:08.938 --> 00:36:10.905
I want to know more.

00:36:18.672 --> 00:36:19.772
[Stout, Dark Chocolate]

00:36:19.772 --> 00:36:20.772
[Wheat Beer, Churros]

00:36:20.772 --> 00:36:22.181
[IPA, Chicken Wings; Lager, Sausage]

00:36:43.372 --> 00:36:45.272
So, how was my recommendation?

00:36:45.272 --> 00:36:48.472
My nickname is Beer Master!

00:36:48.472 --> 00:36:49.572
No, no, no.

00:36:49.572 --> 00:36:52.038
Beer Legend!

00:36:52.038 --> 00:36:54.053
Not sure about legend...

00:36:54.053 --> 00:36:55.813
Hey!

00:36:57.772 --> 00:37:00.438
But isn't this way too much?

00:37:00.438 --> 00:37:04.005
Ah, this is nothing.

00:37:10.821 --> 00:37:16.105
Now, the current high score is 340 points!

00:37:16.872 --> 00:37:19.938
Any more participants
for the basketball game?

00:37:19.938 --> 00:37:22.138
The prizes include

00:37:22.138 --> 00:37:24.505
a premium home-brew beer maker

00:37:24.505 --> 00:37:26.405
and a Love It doll.

00:37:26.405 --> 00:37:28.238
Here you are, come on out, come on out.

00:37:28.238 --> 00:37:29.538
A craft beer brewing machine.

00:37:29.538 --> 00:37:31.205
I really want that.

00:37:31.205 --> 00:37:33.838
- Shall I buy you one?
- Oh, never mind.

00:37:33.838 --> 00:37:36.538
- No need to buy me one.
- Anyone coming?

00:37:36.538 --> 00:37:39.172
Then, why not give it a shot?

00:37:40.372 --> 00:37:41.738
Give it a shot? No way...

00:37:41.738 --> 00:37:44.272
With your height, I bet you're
good at basketball.

00:37:44.272 --> 00:37:46.272
Why do you push so hard?

00:37:49.797 --> 00:37:51.397
Jeez.

00:37:53.253 --> 00:37:55.972
